 take any steps to save At least as my parents say at least we should have done something to save the My parents themselves are not that old and But then they thought that they had already lived enough and did everything they could to save In our apartment the tragedy started on February around five in the I call it a tragedy and I repeat it was a tragedy even though all our family When I recall how they broke down our door my skin crawls even now among Armenians among people who wish me only well I feel like it's all starting over I remember how that mob broke into our apartment My parents were standing in the My father had an axe in his hands and had immediately locked both of the Our door was rarely locked since friends and neighbors often dropped We're known as a hospitable family and we just never really thought about whether the people who were coming to see us were Azerbaijanis Jews or We had friends of many nationalities even a Turkmen My parents were in the hall my father with an I remember him telling my mother Run to the kitchen for a But Mother was detached pale as though she had decided to sell her life a bit To be honest I never expected it of her she's afraid of getting shot and afraid of the A girlfriend was at the house that day a Russian girl Lyuda and Mamma said No matter what happens no matter what they do to us you're not to come out of the We're going to tell them that we're alone in the We went into the There were four of Marina and the Russian girl crawled under the bed and we covered them up with a rug boxes of dishes and Karina and I are standing there and looking at one The idea that perhaps we were seeing each other for the last time flashed somewhere inside I'm an emotional person and I express my emotions I wanted to embrace her and kiss her as though it were the last And maybe Karina was thinking the same thing but she's quite We didn't have time to say anything to each other because we immediately heard Mamma raise a There was so much