 the other room her brother knew what awaited I don't know which one it was Edik or Both of them were in the room from which the axe was But the axe hit one of the people carrying her and so they killed her and made her death even more excruciating maybe the most excruciating of all the deaths of those days in I heard about it all from the neighbor from the Melkumians' His name is Makhaddin he knows my family a He came to see how we had gotten settled in the new apartment in Baku how we were feeling and if we needed He's a good He said You should praise God that you all But what I saw with my own eyes I a man who has seen so many people die who has lived a whole life I he says nearly lost my mind that I had never seen the likes of it and think I never shall The door to his apartment was open and he saw One of the brothers threw the axe because they had already taken the father and mother out of the Igor Edik and Ira He saw Ira naked being carried into the other room in the hands of six or seven He told us about it and said he would never forget He heard the brothers shouting something inarticulate from pain rage and the fact that they were powerless to do But all the same they tried to do The guy who got hit with the axe I I After I had been unsuccessful at killing myself I saw them taking Marina and Lyuda out of the I was in such a state that I couldn't even remember my sister's I wanted to cry Marina out to her but could I looked at her and knew that it was a familiar dear face but couldn't for the life of me remember what her name was and who she And thus I saved her because when they were taking her out she as it turns out had told them that she had just been visiting and that she and Lyuda were both there by chance that they weren't Lyuda's a Russian you can tell right away and Marina speaks Azerbaijani wonderfully and she told them that she was an And I almost gave her away and doomed I'm glad that at least Marina came out of this all in good physical health a